label.value: protein localization to cell periphery

value.value: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, the cell periphery.

label.value: DNA/DNA annealing activity

value.value: An activity that faciliates the formation of a complementary double-stranded DNA molecule.

label.value: mating projection actin fusion focus

value.value: A focus at the mating projection tip where the cell wall is degraded during conjugation with cellular fusion. Actin filaments form an aster-like structure from this location.

label.value: sequence-specific double-stranded DNA binding

value.value: Binding to double-stranded DNA of a specific nucleotide composition, e.g. GC-rich DNA binding, or with a specific sequence motif or type of DNA, e.g. promotor binding or rDNA binding.

label.value: mitotic sister chromatid arm separation

value.value: The cell cycle process in which sister chromatid arms are physically detached from each other during mitosis.

label.value: mitotic chromosome arm condensation

value.value: The cell cycle process in which chromosome arm chromatin structure is compacted prior to and during mitosis in eukaryotic cells.

label.value: mitotic chromosome centromere condensation

value.value: The cell cycle process in which centromere chromatin structure is compacted prior to and during mitosis.

label.value: regulation of protein localization to cell cortex of cell tip

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to cell cortex of cell tip.

label.value: protein localization to cell cortex of cell tip

value.value: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, the cell cortex of the cell tip.

label.value: ribonucleoprotein complex

value.value: A macromolecular complex that contains both RNA and protein molecules.

label.value: double-strand break repair involved in meiotic recombination

value.value: The repair of double-strand breaks in DNA via homologous and nonhomologous mechanisms to reform a continuous DNA helix that contributes to reciprocal meiotic recombination.

label.value: response to amino acid starvation

value.value: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of deprivation of amino acids.

label.value: mitotic metaphase chromosome recapture

value.value: A mechanism to recapture 'lost' chromosomes (chromosomes which have become detached from the spindle) during metaphase of mitotic chromosome segregation. Chromosomes with unattached kinetochores are migrated along (non polar) spindle microtubules to the mitotic spindle pole body by a combination of microtubule depolymerisation and 'kinetochore sliding' (migration of the chromosome along the microtubule). The chromosome subsequently migrates along the polar spindle microtubule to the metaphase plate.

label.value: exit from meiosis

value.value: Any process involved in the progression from anaphase/telophase of meiosis II to the creation of end products of meiosis, in which ploidy is reduced by half.

label.value: metaphase/anaphase transition of meiosis I

value.value: The cell cycle process in which a cell progresses from metaphase to anaphase as part of meiosis I.

label.value: metaphase/anaphase transition of meiosis II

value.value: The cell cycle process in which a cell progresses from metaphase to anaphase as part of meiosis II.

label.value: regulation of DNA damage checkpoint

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a DNA damage checkpoint.

label.value: negative regulation of DNA damage checkpoint

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of a DNA damage checkpoint.

label.value: positive regulation of DNA damage checkpoint

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of a DNA damage checkpoint.

label.value: regulation of protein localization to cell surface

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to the cell surface.

label.value: negative regulation of protein localization to cell surface

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to the cell surface.

label.value: positive regulation of protein localization to cell surface

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to the cell surface.

label.value: regulation of multicellular organismal development

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of multicellular organismal development.

label.value: negative regulation of double-strand break repair via homologous recombination

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of double-strand break repair via homologous recombination.

label.value: regulation of G1/S transition of mitotic cell cycle

value.value: Any signaling pathway that modulates the activity of a cell cycle cyclin-dependent protein kinase to modulate the switch from G1 phase to S phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: Note that this process is usually achieved by the regulation of the G1 cyclin-dependent protein kinase, consider annotating to the child term 'regulation of cyclin-dependent protein kinase activity involved in G1/S ; GO:0031657'.

label.value: regulation of ubiquitin-dependent protein catabolic process

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of ubiquitin-dependent protein catabolic process.

label.value: negative regulation of ubiquitin-dependent protein catabolic process

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of ubiquitin-dependent protein catabolic process.

label.value: positive regulation of ubiquitin-dependent protein catabolic process

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of ubiquitin-dependent protein catabolic process.

label.value: regulation of response to water deprivation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of response to water deprivation.

label.value: negative regulation of DNA-templated DNA replication

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of DNA-dependent DNA replication.

label.value: positive regulation of DNA-templated DNA replication

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of DNA-templated DNA replication.

label.value: regulation of establishment of cell polarity

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of establishment of cell polarity.

label.value: regulation of cysteine-type endopeptidase activity

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cysteine-type endopeptidase activity.

label.value: negative regulation of cysteine-type endopeptidase activity

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cysteine-type endopeptidase activity.

label.value: regulation of removal of superoxide radicals

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of removal of superoxide radicals.

label.value: negative regulation of G1/S transition of mitotic cell cycle

value.value: Any signaling pathway that decreases or inhibits the activity of a cell cycle cyclin-dependent protein kinase to modulate the switch from G1 phase to S phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: regulation of DNA-templated transcription initiation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of DNA-templated transcription initiation.

label.value: negative regulation of DNA-templated transcription initiation

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of DNA-templated transcription initiation.

label.value: positive regulation of DNA-templated transcription initiation

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of DNA-templated transcription initiation.

label.value: regulation of ubiquitin-specific protease activity

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of regulation of ubiquitin-specific protease activity (deubiquitinase) activity.

label.value: negative regulation of ubiquitin-specific protease activity

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of ubiquitin-specific protease (deubiquitinase) activity.

label.value: positive regulation of ubiquitin-specific protease activity

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of ubiquitin-specific protease (deubiquitinase) activity.

label.value: regulation of ribonucleoprotein complex localization

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of ribonucleoprotein complex localization.

label.value: negative regulation of ribonucleoprotein complex localization

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of ribonucleoprotein complex localization.

label.value: positive regulation of ribonucleoprotein complex localization

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of ribonucleoprotein complex localization.

label.value: regulation of proline metabolic process

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of proline metabolic process.

label.value: negative regulation of proline metabolic process

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of proline metabolic process.

label.value: positive regulation of proline metabolic process

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of proline metabolic process.

label.value: regulation of pseudohyphal growth

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of pseudohyphal growth.

label.value: negative regulation of pseudohyphal growth

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of pseudohyphal growth.
